<font color="#FF0000">REMEMBERING</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 13 21:58:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
From time to time I come in here and read the thoughts of others. There is still so much anger here. I went in country in Sept. 67 and left in April 69. U.S.Navy. I was not usually in a direct combat situation so I can only guess what so many of you are going through. I have not been to visit the wall. I really want to go but each time I get close I have to turn back. I was in an outfit in California that de-commisioned and a great number of us went to Nam after that. The luck of something. I knew most of the guys in that squadron I still know the ones I served with But many went to an outfit that got ripped apart in the first two weeks active...... I can't remember one name and it hurts so bad if I spend a lot of time with it. This place helps a bit. Thanks<br>

<p><code>-- bkitsch@tracy.com  (B Kitsch) </code><p>


